---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";
import { SITE } from "@/config";
---

<Layout title={`About | ${SITE.title}`} description="Jack Hughes writes about historical tabletop wargaming — primarily World War 2 — covering battle reports, painted armies, rules reviews, and gaming projects.">
  <Header />
  <main id="main-content" class="app-layout pb-4">
    <h1 class="my-6 text-2xl font-semibold sm:text-3xl">About Battle Lines Drawn</h1>
    <article class="prose max-w-none dark:prose-invert">
      <p>The Battle Lines Drawn blog is the online workspace of Jack Hughes to keep all of his wargaming thoughts and resources in a single silo for later reference. Jack is a keen tabletop wargamer using a variety of wargaming rules and scales.</p>
      <p>Please note that I do not work for any of the wargaming companies mentioned on the blog nor am I affiliated in any way other than somebody who purchases their products and enjoys using them on the tabletop. Any opinions I express about the companies and their rules are entirely my opinion as a fan of these rules. I have never received any of the products mentioned here for free or at discounted rates. I pay exactly the same price as you probably have.</p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
